div.font: Template method - Use an abstract class that defines templates to execute its methods,
and subclasses may override the implementation.

Bridge - An interface which acts as a bridge, which makes the functionality of concrete classes
independent from interface implementer classes,
where both types of classes can be altered structurally without affecting each other.
Factory - Method that creates new objects without specifying the exact class type
Chain of responsibility - Let different receivers handle a request as a chain.
Module - Group multiple related elements (classes, methods, interfaces) as one singular module.

div.span: - Use different interface implementations to define how an action should be made.

div.font:
Decorator - Create a decorator class to wrap another class' functionality and provides additional
functionality to the original class without changing its signature.
Observer - If one object is modified, its dependent objects are to be notified automatically
Facade - Hide complexity behind oftentimes one singular class and expose functionality through class methods.
State - Change behavior as an internal state is changed.
Adapter - Adapts functionality of one interface to another
MVC - Model that handles data, View that visualises data from the model, Controller that acts on model from
the view, and handles data for the view
